            <h1>The Futures of Typography</h1>
            <div class="intro">
              <p>
                Typesetting on the web has evolved from a quirky afterthought
                into an invaluable practice. Within a span of twenty years
                complex interfaces that adapt to their environment, as well as
                an overwhelming number of typefaces, have bloomed all around us.
                Likewise, using animations and transitions or balancing display
                text in conjunction with powerful OpenType features became not
                only possible but expected. So where do we go from here? What
                are the skills we need to contribute to the future of
                typography? And what do two ghostly figures from the 15th
                century have to do with that future?
